items.description: Lonny Greenberg and Stefan Miller are brothers from another mother who will open your mind to sports in a way that you may not have realized you were missing.   Two Dads from Philly and New York who somehow ended up in South Florida.  We have played sports, pee wee, little league, high school, we have attended countless historical sporting events and we absolutely love talking about sports.  Look, we aren‚Äôt former players nor are we going to breakdown games because there are enough people doing that already.  What we will do is remind you why you love sports, open up some old wounds because sports is pain and have kids share their opinions with us because the next generation is really important.  This podcast will take you into the heart of sports and why you became a fan in the first place.

items.description: Welcome to our DevOps Career Podcast, the ultimate guide for those interested in starting or advancing their career in DevOps.In this podcast, we provide expert advice and insights from industry professionals on everything you need to know about DevOps, including the latest trends, tools, and best practices.Whether you're just starting out or looking to take your DevOps career to the next level, we've got you covered. Each episode is packed with practical tips, real-world examples, and actionable advice to help you succeed in this fast-paced and rapidly-evolving field.From mastering key skills and building your DevOps toolkit to networking and getting certified, we cover it all. Join us on this journey as we explore the world of DevOps and help you build the career of your dreams.

items.description: During each episode of the ACDIS Podcast, the ACDIS team chats with a special guest, including industry thought leaders, ACDIS advisory board members, and CDI specialists. You'll hear about best practices, tips, and the latest ACDIS and CDI news. This lively 30-minute program will keep CDI and HIM professionals entertained and up to date on the pulse of the CDI industry.   Tune in every other Wednesday at 11:30 a.m. ET to listen live or catch the recording on our website or via your podcast app!
